Nadal did save two break points, including when he was serving for the match. He next plays either Andrey Golubev of Kazakhstan or 17-year-old Croatian wildcard  Borna Coric on Friday.

It was even easier for Federer, who broke Muller in the sixth game and wrapped up the first set in 25 minutes, winning 91 percent of his first-serve points.

The second set was even quicker as Federer totally dominated Muller, who failed to win a single point on Federer's serve, as the 17-time Grand Slam champion's ninth ace took him to match point.

Federer, who improved to 5-0 against Muller in career head-to-heads, next plays Denis Istomin of Uzbekistan and leads him 5-0 too.

